The paper discusses interpretability approaches for blackbox classifiers, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the assumptions made by these approaches, which is related to the field of computer ethics (cs.CE) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of these approaches in image classification (cs.CV).
